noe is a simple note-taking application built on top of ErlyWeb

INSTALLATIION

1. Install yaws, http://yaws.hyber.org
2. Install MySQL, http://mysql.org
3. Install ErlyWeb, http://erlyweb.org

4. Create a site in your yaws.conf file:

	<server noe>
	        port = 80
	        listen = 0.0.0.0
	        docroot = /path/to/noe/www/
	        appmods = </, erlyweb>

	        <opaque>
	                appname = noe
	        </opaque>
	</server>

5. Edit /etc/hosts (on Windows - /path/to/windows/system32/drivers/etc/hosts) and add:
	
	127.0.0.1	noe

5. Run migrations/main.sql to create necessary tables in you database
6. Edit src/noe_app.hrl and change database connection data and paths
7. Open console, compile src/noe.erl. It may be done like so:
  
	sh> cd /path/to/noe
	../noe> erl
	1> c(noe).
	{ok, noe}
	2> halt().

8. Place the generated noe.beam file somwhere where yaws can see it. You can add a ebin_dir to yaws.conf:
	
	ebin_dir = /path/to/my/beam/files
	
9. Open console, run yaws, run noe
	
	sh> yaws -i
	... lots of info ...
	1> noe:start().
	... noe is compiling ...
	
10. You can now open up your browser and navigate to http://noe/